{"parse":{"title":"Blackfathom Deeps","pageid":13956,"wikitext":{"*":"{{infobox instance\n|name=Blackfathom Deeps\n|aka=BFD\n|ss=Blackfathom Deeps loading screen.jpg\n|caption=Blackfathom Deeps loading graphic\n|loc=[[The Zoram Strand]], [[Ashenvale]]\n|race={{Race|Dwarf }}<br />{{Race|Gnome }}<br />{{Race|Human }}<br />{{Race|Makrura }}<br />{{Race|Murloc }}<br />{{Race|Naga }}<br />{{Race|Orc }}<br />{{Race|Satyr }}\n|boss=[[Aku'mai]]\n|type=\n|level=20-30\n|minlevel=15\n|players=5 (10)\n|key=\n|bosses= {{Blackfathom Deeps}}\n}}\n[[File:BFDbosses.jpg|thumb|Blackfathom Deeps bosses]]\n'''Blackfathom Deeps'''{{coords|15|15|Ashenvale}} is a partially underwater dungeon in northwestern [[Ashenvale]]. It is accessed by a stair-lined shaft that requires one to swim through an underwater entrance. The depths are comprised of a series of watery caverns leading deep to a temple devoted to the [[Old Gods]]. The [[Twilight's Hammer]] cult runs this shrine, and it has joined forces with local [[naga]] and [[satyr]]s to defend the unholy creature, [[Aku'mai]]. It seems an Old God may be underneath the land.<ref>{{quest|Blackfathom Villainy}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThis series of ruins and caverns was built into the side of a cliff directly south of [[Black Fathom Bay]]. Many dangerous creatures lurk within - including, if tales at the [[Fish Eye Tavern]] are to believed, ghosts of heroes that fell to some nastiness while within the Deeps. Others suggest that this place, once a night elf temple to [[Elune]], is now the headquarters of the vile warlocks, known as the [[Shadow Council]].<ref name=\"Dungeons & Dragons Warcraft The Roleplaying Game 194\">''[[Dungeons & Dragons Warcraft The Roleplaying Game]]'', pg. 194</ref> The naga here seem to be searching for something. The Twilight\u2019s Hammer, a foul cult dedicated to the Old Gods, works with the naga in the underground ruins for an unknown purpose.<ref name=\"Lands of Mystery 8\">''[[Lands of Mystery]]'', pg. 8</ref>\n\n{{wow-dungeons}}\n:''Situated along the [[Zoram Strand]] of [[Ashenvale]], Blackfathom Deeps was once a glorious temple dedicated to the night elves' moon-goddess, [[Elune]]. However, the great Sundering shattered the temple - sinking it beneath the waves of the [[Veiled Sea]]. There it remained untouched - until, drawn by its ancient power - the [[naga]] and [[satyr]] emerged to plumb its secrets. Legends hold that the ancient beast, [[Aku'mai]], has taken up residence within the temple's ruins. [[Aku'mai]], a favored pet of the primordial [[Old Gods]], has preyed upon the area ever since. Drawn to Aku'mai's presence, the cult known as the [[Twilight's Hammer]] has also come to bask in the Old Gods' evil presence.''\n\n==Geography==\n===Maps===\n<gallery>\nFile:WorldMap-BlackFathomDeeps1.jpg\nFile:WorldMap-BlackFathomDeeps2.jpg\nFile:WorldMap-BlackFathomDeeps3.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n===Sub-regions===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n||[[Aku'mai's Lair]]|| \u2022 ||[[The Drowned Sacellum]]|| \u2022 ||[[The Forgotten Pool]]|| \u2022 ||[[Moonshrine Ruins]]|| \u2022 ||[[Moonshrine Sanctum]]|| \u2022 ||[[Pool of Ask'ar|The Pool of Ask'ar]]||\n|}\n\n==Inhabitants==\n;Quest givers\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Ashelan Northwood|icon=NightElf Male}}\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Relwyn Shadestar|icon=NightElf Female}}\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Sentinel Aluwyn|icon=NightElf Female}}\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Sentinel-trainee Issara|icon=NightElf Female}}\n*{{NPC|Alliance|Scout Thaelrid|icon=NightElf Male}}\n*{{NPC|Horde|Je'neu Sancrea|icon=Troll Male}}\n*{{NPC|Horde|Zeya|icon=Troll Female}}\n*{{NPC|Horde|Flaming Eradicator|icon=Fire}}\n\n==Quest guide==\n;Current quests\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n! Quest name\n! Quest giver\n! Zone location\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|{{Alliance Icon Small}} Alliance quests\n|-\n| {{questlong|Alliance|24|Blackfathom Deeps (Alliance1)|Blackfathom Deeps}}\n| {{NPC|Alliance|Shindrell Swiftfire|icon=NightElf Female}}\n| [[Blackfathom Camp]], [[Ashenvale]]\n|-\n| {{questlong|Alliance|24|Blackfathom Deeps (Alliance2)|Blackfathom Deeps}}\n| {{NPC|Alliance|Raene Wolfrunner|icon=NightElf Female}}\n| [[Astranaar]], [[Ashenvale]]\n|-\n| {{questlong|Alliance|28|Blackfathom Villainy (Alliance)|Blackfathom Villainy}}\n| {{NPC|Alliance|Scout Thaelrid|icon=NightElf Male}}\n| alcove in [[Blackfathom Deeps]]\n|-\n| {{questlong|Alliance|25|In Search of Thaelrid}}\n| {{NPC|Alliance|Ashelan Northwood|icon=NightElf Male}}\n| [[Blackfathom Deeps]] entrance\n|-\n| {{questlong|Alliance|25|Knowledge in the Deeps}}\n| {{NPC|Alliance|Sentinel-trainee Issara|icon=NightElf Female}}\n| [[Blackfathom Deeps]] entrance\n|-\n| {{questlong|Alliance|26|Researching the Corruption}}\n| {{NPC|Alliance|Relwyn Shadestar|icon=NightElf Female}}\n| [[Blackfathom Deeps]] entrance\n|-\n| {{questlong|Alliance|28|Twilight Falls}}\n| {{NPC|Alliance|Sentinel Aluwyn|icon=NightElf Female}}\n| [[Blackfathom Deeps]] entrance\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|{{Horde Icon Small}} Horde quests\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|24|Blackfathom Deeps (Horde)|Blackfathom Deeps}}\n| {{NPC|Horde|Commander Grimfang|icon=Orc Male}}\n| [[Zoram'gar Outpost]], [[Ashenvale]]\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|22|The Essence of Aku'Mai}}\n| {{NPC|Horde|Dagrun Ragehammer|icon=Orc Male}}\n| [[Zoram'gar Outpost]], [[Ashenvale]]\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|26|Amongst the Ruins}}\n| {{NPC|Horde|Je'neu Sancrea|icon=Troll Male}}\n| [[Blackfathom Deeps]] entrance\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|27|Nightmare of the Deeps}}\n| {{NPC|Horde|Je'neu Sancrea|icon=Troll Male}}\n| [[Blackfathom Deeps]] entrance\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|26|Deep in the Deeps}}\n| {{NPC|Horde|Zeya|icon=Troll Female}}\n| [[Blackfathom Deeps]] entrance\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|28|The Enemy of My Enemy (BFD)|The Enemy of My Enemy}}\n| {{NPC||Flaming Eradicator|icon=Fire}}\n| [[Blackfathom Deeps]]\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|30|Baron Aquanis}}\n| {{item|Strange Water Globe|icon=}}, drop<br />from [[Baron Aquanis]]\n| In Blackfathom Deeps\n|}\n\n;Removed quests\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n! Quest name\n! Quest giver\n! Zone location\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|{{Horde Icon Small}} Horde quests\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|22|Trouble in the Deeps}} (pre-req)\n| {{RaceIconExt|Water|Small}}{{NPC|Horde|Tsunaman}}\n| [[Sun Rock Retreat]], [[Stonetalon Mountains]]\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|22|Allegiance to the Old Gods}}\n| [[File:INV Misc Note 06.png|20px]]{{loot|Common|Damp Note}}, drop<br />from [[Blackfathom Tide Priestess]]\n| Outside the instance\n|-\n| {{questlong|Horde|26|Allegiance to the Old Gods (2)}}\n| {{RaceIcon|Troll|Male|Small}}{{NPC|Horde|Je'neu Sancrea}}\n| [[Zoram'gar Outpost]], [[Ashenvale]]\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|{{Neutral Icon Small}} Class specific quests\n|-\n| |{{questclass|Neutral|Warlock|20|The Orb of Soran'ruk}}\n| {{RaceIcon|Human|Male|Small}}{{NPC|Neutral|Doan Karhan}}\n| East of [[Camp Taurajo]], [[the Barrens]]\n|-\n| | {{questclass|Alliance|Paladin|22|Seeking the Kor Gem}}\n| {{RaceIcon|NightElf|Male|Small}}{{NPC|Alliance|Thundris Windweaver}}\n| [[Auberdine]], [[Darkshore]]\n|-\n| | {{questclass|Horde|Paladin|23|The Path of the Adept}}\n| {{RaceIcon|BloodElf|Male|Small}}{{NPC|Horde|Knight-Lord Bloodvalor}}\n| [[Farstriders' Square]], [[Silvermoon]]\n|}\n\n==Walkthrough==\nThis underwater cove can be tricky to navigate for the first time, but it's a great place to hone your skills and find your role when in a group.\n\nLevel appropriate groups should watch out for two things. The first is that there are many magic casting Naga which, when amassed in numbers, can do a good deal of damage. Always keep a warrior with shield bash on any casting mobs, or any other class that can stun/interrupt like Shamans and Paladins. Also, this is a great dungeon to try out crowd control. Many of the enemies pulled to you will come with friends. In addition, there are invisible Satyr that you cannot see until they have come close enough to aggro you. \n\nCaution should be used when combating the murlocs. Once at low health, they run quite fast, often running back towards the other murlocs and the murloc boss Gelihast. Keep a form of snare on these guys.  The latter part of the instance includes the Twilight Cultists. These foes come in groups of two or three, but often can include more if you aren't aware of wanderers. The ideal way to avoid an unwanted add is to pull with range, targeting the casters first (which you can get to follow you by cutting the Line of Sight, i.e. turning around a corner), and sheeping, sapping, or off tanking the adds. Also, having the highest level person in your group do the pulling helps, due to their smaller aggro radius. \n\nThe 'summoning chamber' with Twilight Lord Kelris includes many other cultists in the room. It is recommended to use the walled off entrance to your advantage, pulling the mobs one by one from the large room until Kelris is alone. After the room is cleared, he is ready to be engaged safely. Once he is defeated, all four candles pieces on the middle altar will need to be lit in order to advance past the large door to the final boss. Right-click these one at a time because a small group of mobs is summoned from the adjacent doors every time you do. Defeat these one at a time to avoid death.\n\nThe final boss is relatively easy if you have a dedicated tank and healer. See walk-through for [[Aku'mai]]. A stylishly hatted dwarf will await you at the end, giving Alliance players an option to port to [[Darnassus]].\n\n==Resources==\n*[[Herbalism|Herbs]]\n**{{item|Bruiseweed|icon=}}\n**{{item|Stranglekelp|icon=}}\n*[[Mining|Ore Veins]]\n**{{item|Tin Ore|icon=}}\n\n==Dungeon denizens==\n*{{RaceIconExt|Crab|Small}} [[Crab]]s\n*{{RaceIcon|DarkIron|Male|Small}} [[Dark Iron dwarves]] (one, [[Morridune]])\n*{{RaceIcon|Dwarf|Male|Small}}{{RaceIcon|Dwarf|Female|Small}}[[Dwarves]]\n*{{RaceIcon|Undead|Male|Small}}{{RaceIcon|Undead|Female|Small}}[[Forsaken]]\n*{{RaceIcon|Gnome|Male|Small}}{{RaceIcon|Gnome|Female|Small}}[[Gnome]]s\n*{{RaceIcon|Human|Male|Small}}{{RaceIcon|Human|Female|Small}}[[Human]]s\n*{{RaceIconExt|Hydra|Small}} [[Hydra]]s (one, [[Aku'mai]])\n*{{RaceIconExt|Makrura|Small}} [[Makrura]]\n*{{RaceIconExt|Murloc|Small}} [[Murloc]]s\n*{{RaceIcon|Naga|Male|Small}}{{RaceIcon|Naga|Female|Small}}[[Naga]]\n*{{RaceIcon|NightElf|Male|Small}} [[Night elves]] (one, [[Argent Guard Thaelrid]])\n*{{RaceIcon|Orc|Male|Small}}{{RaceIcon|Orc|Female|Small}}[[Orc]]s\n*{{RaceIconExt|Satyr|Small}} [[Satyr]]\n*{{RaceIcon|Tauren|Male|Small}}{{RaceIcon|Tauren|Female|Small}}[[Tauren]]\n*{{RaceIconExt|Threshadon|Small}} [[Threshadon]]s\n*{{RaceIconExt|Turtle|Small}} [[Turtle]]s\n*{{RaceIcon|Troll|Male|Small}}{{RaceIcon|Troll|Female|Small}}[[Troll]]s\n*{{RaceIconExt|Water|Small}} [[Water Elemental]]s\n\n===Encounters===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Bosses || Monsters\n|- valign=top\n|\n* '''Drowned Sacellum\n|\n* {{NPC||Blindlight Murloc}}\n* {{NPC||Murkshallow Snapclaw}}\n* {{NPC||Skittering Crustacean}}\n|- valign=top class=\"alt\"\n|\n* '''Pool of As'kar\n**{{RaceIconExt|Turtle|Small}} {{NPC||Ghamoo-ra}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Aku'mai Fisher}}\n* {{NPC||Blackfathom Myrmidon}}\n* {{NPC||Blackfathom Sea Witch}}\n* {{NPC||Snapping Crustacean}}\n|- valign=top\n|\n* '''Pool of As'kar - Side Cavern\n**{{RaceIconExt|Naga_Female|Small}} {{NPC||Lady Sarevess}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Blackfathom Myrmidon}}\n* {{NPC||Blackfathom Sea Witch}}\n|- valign=top class=\"alt\"\n|\n* '''Tunnels\n**{{RaceIconExt|Human_Male|Small}} {{NPC||Lorgus Jett}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Blackfathom Myrmidon}}\n* {{NPC||Blackfathom Sea Witch}}\n* {{NPC||Fallenroot Hellcaller}}\n* {{NPC||Fallenroot Shadowstalker}}\n* {{NPC||Twilight Acolyte}}\n* {{NPC||Twilight Reaver}}\n|- valign=top\n|\n* '''Shrine of Gelihast\n**{{RaceIconExt|Murloc|Small}} {{NPC||Gelihast}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Blindlight Muckdweller}}\n* {{NPC||Blindlight Oracle}}\n|- valign=top class=\"alt\"\n|\n* '''Moonshrine Ruins\n**{{RaceIconExt|Water|Small}} {{NPC||Baron Aquanis}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Aqua Guardian}}\n* {{NPC||Barbed Crustacean}}\n* {{NPC||Deep Pool Threshfin}}\n* {{NPC||Twilight Acolyte}}\n* {{NPC||Twilight Aquamancer}}\n* {{NPC||Twilight Loreseeker}}\n* {{NPC||Twilight Reaver}}\n|- valign=top\n|\n* '''Forgotten Pool\n**{{RaceIconExt|Threshadon|Small}} {{NPC||Old Serra'kis}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Deep Pool Threshfin}}\n|- valign=top class=\"alt\"\n|\n* '''Moonshrine Sanctum\n**{{RaceIconExt|Orc_Male|Small}} {{NPC||Twilight Lord Kelris}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Aku'mai Servant}}\n* {{NPC||Aku'mai Snapjaw}}\n* {{NPC||Barbed Crustacean}}\n* {{NPC||Murkshallow Softshell}}\n* {{NPC||Twilight Elementalist}}\n* {{NPC||Twilight Shadowmage}}\n* {{NPC||Voidwalker Minion}}\n|- valign=top\n|\n* '''Aku'mai's Lair\n**{{RaceIconExt|Hydra|Small}} {{NPC||Aku'mai}}\n|\n* {{NPC||Aku'mai Snapjaw}}\n|- valign=top class=\"alt\"\n|}\n\n==Loot==\nSee [[Blackfathom Deeps loot]].\n\n==Notes ==\n* Also known as: BFD (not to be confused with BRD, which is [[Blackrock Depths]].)\n** Sometimes misidentified as Blackfathom ''Depths''.\n* Found in: Ashenvale Forest, Northwest corner (The [[Zoram Strand]])\n* Enemy Level Range:\n** Outside Instance: 20-21\n** Inside Instance: 18-25 (Elite)\n* Gain entrance at level: 15\n* 10 Player Limit (However quests can only be completed with 5 - which is how it is most often tackled)\n\n==Patches changes==\n* {{Patch 4.0.3a|note=Quest givers placed inside entrance.}}\n* {{Patch 1.3.0|note=\n**Capped at ten players.\n**Characters dying in the instanced portions of Blackfathom Deeps will now correctly receive a corpse marker in the minimap and see the message letting them know that they need to enter the instance before they will be able to resurrect.}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n<!-- Read http://www.wowwiki.com/WoWWiki:External_links before posting your links here.\nLinks that do not conform to the rules will be DELETED.\nRepeat violations may result in a BAN.\nHave a nice day. :) -->\n{{bnetwowinstance|{{PAGENAME}}}}\n{{elinks-zone|719}}\n\n\n{{Blackfathom Deeps Subzones}}\n{{Ashenvale}}\n{{Dungeons}}\n\n[[es:Blackfathom Deeps]]\n[[fr:Profondeurs de Brassenoire]]\n[[ja:Blackfathom Deeps]]\n[[pl:Blackfathom Deeps]]\n\n[[Category:Instances]]\n[[Category:Caves]]\n[[Category:Blackfathom Deeps| ]]\n[[Category:Old Gods]]\n[[Category:Ruins]]"}}}